<L>__{exterior of clay shaw's house new orleans(1967)}
<A>__{jim, lou, al, numa and several policemen stand at the door as clay shaw comes to it.}
<C>__{lou}
<D>__{mr. shaw, you're under arrest, charged with conspiracy and entering into an agreement with other persons for the specific purpose of committing the crime of murder of president john f. kennedy in violation of...}
<A>__{the voice dropping away as the devastated look on shaw's face spreads, sickly, undone, his arrogant public composure gone, face now filled with terror, disbelief.}
<C>__{lou}
<D>__{...we have a warrant to search the premises.}
<A>__{the policemen take shaw while the d.a. staff moves into the carriage house past the butler, frankie jenkins.}
<C>__{inside shaw's house}
<D>__{in the bedroom, numa points out to jim the hooks screwed into the ceiling. al pulls out five whips, several lengths of chain, a black hood and matching black cape. dried blood is on one whip.}
